I am probably going to write way too much here, but this actually touches on something I think a lot about, what makes for good vs bad storytelling.  I love when a world I'm immersed in makes a thorough attempt to make sure that the rules of the story are consistent with the rules of the world.  Nothing throws me out of the story faster than if something is inconsistent.  If I had picked any of the other options and somehow escaped, I would have felt the outcome was bad, because I did NOT have the skills necessary to complete said outcome.

Thanks for this, this was an amazing HIT on a rainy Saturday.
